<item>
            <title>[LU-9085] Fix &quot;Using a hash as a reference is deprecated&quot; in llstat</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9085</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The customer reported the following issue in SFW-18:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[root@mt2-oss2 ~]# llstat -i 5 home-OST0001
Using a hash as a reference is deprecated at /usr/bin/llstat line 58.
Using a hash as a reference is deprecated at /usr/bin/llstat line 85.
Using a hash as a reference is deprecated at /usr/bin/llstat line 121.
Using a hash as a reference is deprecated at /usr/bin/llstat line 122.
/usr/bin/llstat: STATS on 02/01/17 /proc/fs/lustre/obdfilter/home-OST0001/stats on 10.55.150.13@o2ib
snapshot_time 1485997519.917824
read_bytes 78435913
write_bytes 81111225
setattr 71805
punch 64
sync 195530
destroy 272792
create 2295
statfs 285218
get_info 4
quotactl 16
set_info_async 1
connect 220
disconnect 133
Illegal division by zero at /usr/bin/llstat line 80, &amp;lt;STATS&amp;gt; line 15.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will create a patch to fix that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
